-- China Railway Construction First-Quarter Profit Rises 47% to $205 Million
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-04-26T22:49:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/china-railway-construction-first-quarter-profit-rises-47-to-205-million.html

          
          
             China Railway Construction Corp.
said first-quarter net income rose 47 percent from a year
earlier to 1.4 billion yuan, according to a filing to Shanghai’s
stock exchange. Sales gained 37 percent to 70 billion yuan,
according to the statement.  
 The company’s 2009 annual profit increased to 6.6 billion
yuan from 3.6 billion yuan in 2008, China Railway Construction
said in a separate statement. Sales rose to 355.5 billion yuan
last year from 226.1 billion yuan in 2008, it said.  
